@homegrowninmusic / At your service by @dappesst 
—
“We’ve sort of waited two and a half years to put out this album, no big deal. It’s been a wild ride. There was actually no specific concept to this particular album, we just wanted to experiment with as many styles as we possibly could. The album is reflective of how we like to celebrate and appreciate global music culture and in doing so, incorporating our own original sound to it. We decided to name the album “At Your Service” with a reason to serve the listener a platter of a wide range of genres with the intention of showcasing our versatility. It was really tough to bring about the balance between maintaining the authenticity of a genre yet moulding it into our own sound.”
- Dappest & adL 
On the album “At Your Service”

#HGSFashion / Margn’s SS/ FW-22
@margnworld 
—
About:

With the world on move and displacements becoming more painful than ever, Margn’s SS/FW-22 exemplifies the perilous journeys of immigrants, especially refugees and their trajectories of displacement, their suffering, need, and their courage to keep going on. This collection aims at sparking a conversation on whether borders and divisions precede being human. Breaking artificial hierarchies and social constructs, a culture is proposed – a culture where humanity precedes everything. The concept is knitted to clothing through symbolic compositions, humanoid symbols, uniforms of humanity, signature argyle patterns, valves and upcycled water pipes representing the interconnectedness amongst all of us. These ideas are presented alongside a language of sartorial tailoring and redefined knitwear.

About the Brand:
Founded at the brink of a global humanitarian crisis in 2020, focuses on human-centred design to bring home the fact that despite and beyond perceived differences, we are all humans . The ‘human’ beyond any boundaries forms the core of the ergonomics of its products as also the conception and production of collections. With a focus on exploring unfamiliar cultures, Margn brings unconventional staples rendered for the future of humanity. A humanoid shape (akin to the one used in the  Margn’s symbol) is used throughout its design to create symbolic patterns that evoke emotions, mirroring the core concept of each collection.

#HGStreet / ‘Imaginarium - Another World’ by @weargigai 
—
Another World:
We often introspect, what if a portal to our imaginative world were a possibility. Possibilities that know no end with Surrealism. A real world within this glory of imagination, paving a path to an alternate world – “Another World “ 

Another World is our leap beyond the realm of our bags. With real world imagery of our products as a constant, we bring to you a glimpse of our world - a cinematic into our imaginative universe.

About Gigai:
The House of Gigai is a multi-disciplinary force from a new world - one in which ancient crafts intersect with innovative technology and contemporary techniques. The brand creates accessories that are audacious modern relics of one's stories and fantasies. With a focus of reinventing indigenous crafts with technology, the vernacular of the brand is a symbiotic relationship between geometric expression and nature's organic form, flavoured with fantasy.
.
.
#HomegrownIn #Fashion #aesthetic #visualart #artistsoninstagram

#HGSPhotography / Art by @aanchalrai.1
—
About the project:
In India everything we do has a maximalist approach to it.
From our ornate architecture to our big fat indian weddings
to our food to our dresses we love colour, we love
celebrating! No matter what social strata we come from we
all truly love the same things.
So how do you stand out in a country of 1.3 billion people?
How do you pay homage to a great nation and its history?
You run free, wild on the streets.
Soaking in every bit of the city.

About the Artist :
A twenty year something fashion stylist, art director and
founder of studio WorkinGrl
